READ: White House Guidelines To States For ReopeningEnlarge this image toggle caption Saul Loeb/AFP via Getty Images Saul Loeb/AFP via Getty ImagesPresident Trump spoke to governors Thursday, outlining recommendations for states to reopen based on several factors.
The Trump administration has shared a guideline of three phases for states to begin easing social distancing measures and stay-at-home orders, according to a copy of the guidelines obtained by NPR's Tamara Keith.
The guidelines come after a number of governors formed coalitions to work together to restart their respective economies.
Trump and the coronavirus task force are speaking about the guidelines Thursday afternoon at the White House.
